column5: Today on Tuesday October 12th I decided to hit the water for some fall largemouths!! The bite was very very slow compared to ussual we fished and fished tried everything and was only able to land 5 decent ones in the boat but i'll tell you one thing what a nice day it was , no wind , sunny and no clouds at all... We enjoyed our day very much even if we only got 5 fish into the boat plus we saw a cow moose  !! Here's a picture of what we caught...    Get out there and have some fun don't forget the Yum dingers for some Fall largemouth bass fishing !
awesome post dude! you are posting quite a bit of content with only 14 posts! congrats on lots of fishing time!
Well done for this time of the year.....
wow so jealous haha. Great largies buddy!

I'm assuming you caught those in Nipissing? They have been introducing Largies to cater to American clients, and it looks like the population is doing well! I have to drive up there one of these days! Thanks for sharing.
Nope they're not from Nipissing! It's a small Largemouth Bass/Pike lake about 30 min from home
Great picks of some nice Largies!!  Thanks
I'm going to have to get up there to Sturgeon Falls
